<h2>Overview</h2><p>Installing a new fuel tank skid plate can seem like an intimidating task, but with the right approach, it can be accomplished relatively easily. In this article, we’ll walk through the installation of the Rock Hard 4X4 fuel tank skid plate for the 2015 Jeep Wrangler JK Unlimited. Not only will you learn the installation process, but you may find some helpful tips along the way.</p><h2>What This Covers</h2><p>This guide will detail the steps necessary to install the RH4X4 skid plate, including:</p><ul><li>Removing the factory skid plate</li><li>Managing the fuel tank while keeping it in place</li><li>Cleaning and preparing the area for installation</li><li>Attaching the new skid plate effectively</li></ul><h2>Step-by-Step Breakdown</h2><ol><li><strong>Preparing the Workspace:</strong> Before starting, make sure to work in a well-lit area. A clean driveway or garage is preferable to avoid losing small parts.</li><li><strong>Gathering Tools:</strong> You’ll need a variety of tools for this install, such as wrenches, sockets, and, ideally, some straps to hold up the fuel tank while you work.</li><li><strong>Removing the Factory Skid Plate:</strong> This involves loosening the bolts that hold the factory skid in place. It’s important to ensure that the fuel tank is properly supported during this process, as the skid plate also acts as a mounting bracket.</li><li><strong>Cleaning Up:</strong> Once the factory skid is removed, take the opportunity to clean the area. This might include using some rust treatment on the factory skid and anything else you can reach while it’s out. Don’t skip this step; a clean surface allows for better adhesion and longevity.</li><li><strong>Installing the New Skid:</strong> While the factory hanger is out, consider pre-installing the new skid plate to avoid difficulties later. Be sure to align the holes properly, as drilling them requires precision.</li><li><strong>Securing Everything:</strong> Now, hoist the combined skid and hanger back into place. This might require some muscle, especially if you’re doing it alone. Ensure all bolts are secured to the proper torque specifications.</li></ol><h2>Helpful Tips</h2><ul><li>For ease of installation, aim to do this job when your tank is less than a quarter full. This will reduce the weight and make handling much easier.</li><li>If working under the vehicle, always ensure that you have jack stands in place to prevent any accidents.</li><li>When drilling into the factory part to install the new skid, be cautious to avoid damaging the fuel tank itself. The risk is minimal if you know where the tank is located.</li><li>Consider using a friend to help with lifting and bolts; some parts can be unwieldy.</li></ul><h2>Key Takeaways</h2><p>Installing a fuel tank skid plate is a vital upgrade for those who frequently take their Jeep off-road. Not only does it provide additional protection to the fuel tank, but it can also enhance the overall durability of your rig. While the process can involve some heavy lifting, proper planning and execution will make your installation go smoothly. Don't forget to take time to clean your components, as this can lead to better results and longevity for the parts involved.</p>

